MELT butter in large skillet. Add pork; cook, turning once, until no longer pink in center. Transfer to serving plate; keep warm. ADD shallots to skillet; cook, stirring frequently, until tender. Stir in nectar, sherry, maple syrup and bouillon. Bring to a boil; cook, stirring frequently, until sauce has thickened. Remove from heat; pour sauce over pork. Sprinkle with apricots and parsley.